																								 New Delhi, Nov. 21: Germany-based business software provider SAP will raise its headcount to 7,000 in the next two years in the country from 4,790. India is now the third largest country for SAP in terms of employee strength. We plan to increase our india headcount to 7,000 in a couple of years, said Ranjan Das, president and ceo of SAP India. The company, which added 714 clients between July-September 2007, has also doubled its revenues in the country.																								 Mumbai, Nov. 21: Religare Enterprises plans to enter the asset management business. We have applied for the asset management business. We are expecting approval from market regulator Sebi, Religare ceo and managing director, Sunil Godhwani said on the sidelines of the companys listing ceremony. Religare shares got listed at a premium of 75 per cent over the issue price of Rs 185 a share on the BSE. 																								 Mumbai, Nov. 21: Punjab National Banks board has approved the merger of pnb Gilts with itself. Pnb Gilts may prepare a scheme of its merger with the bank and seek necessary approvals, the bank informed the BSE.																								 Mumbai, Nov. 21: Indra Nooyi, PepsiCos chief executive officer, has been appointed as a director on the board of the US-India Business Council, the premier business advocacy organisation representing 250 of the largest US companies investing in India and two dozen of Indias largest global companies. 																								 New Delhi, Nov. 21: The government has no plans to appoint a regulator for labour conditions in bpo companies, labour minister Oscar Fernandes said. Since labour laws are already applicable to the bpos and are regulated accordingly, the ministry has no proposal to appoint a regulator for bpo companies, he said.																								 New Delhi, Nov. 21:The parliamentary standing committee on tourism has recommended the government to rationalise taxes on hotels, food, beverages and aviation fuel to promote India as a value-for-money destination.
